<h2 class="web">Discs</h2>
<p>Do you want to purchase additional DDC European Open DDC discs? We
have them for sale at the registration desk, 10 euros per disc. Payment
methods: Cash or MobilePay app.</p>
</section>
<section id="public-transport" class="level2 web">
<h2 class="web">Public Transport</h2>
<p>We recommend using public transport (HSL) to reach the venue. Here’s
a <a
href="https://reittiopas.hsl.fi/reitti/-/Purotie%208%2C%20it%C3%A4inen%2C%20Helsinki%3A%3A60.215522%2C24.868068?arriveBy=true&amp;locale=en&amp;setTime=true&amp;time=1784955600">pre-filled
journey planner link</a> for checking travel times from wherever you’re
staying.</p>
<p>Some practical notes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Buy tickets in the <strong>HSL app</strong> or from ticket machines
— you cannot buy tickets on board.</li>
<li>The venue and central Helsinki are both in <strong>zone AB</strong>.
Helsinki Airport is in zone C, so buy an <strong>ABC ticket</strong>
when arriving from or heading to the airport.</li>
<li>Single tickets are valid for 80–90 minutes depending on zones; day
tickets are worth considering for the weekend.</li>
</ul>
